<TITLE> Jalil undergoes 17 medical tests </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, June 4 (bdnews24.com) -- Detained Awami League general secretary Abdul Jalil has undergone at least 17 medical tests, a jail official said Monday. The AL leader is now under supervision of Professor Fazlur Rahman in the coronary care unit of Bangabandhu Sheikh Mujib Medical University Hospital. Major Shamsul Haider Siddiqui, deputy inspector general (prisons), told bdnews24.com that Jalil was suffering from diabetes and heart ailments. Doctors prescribed 17 tests to find out what was wrong with him, he said. Siddiqui said doctors would decide on how long Jalil has to stay in hospital. Jalil's wife Rehana Jalil and four other family members met him at the hospital Monday morning. A security guard at the CCU, Belal Hossain, told bdnews24.com that Jalil's relatives came to hospital at about 9.30am and stayed for 15 minutes. Jalil was taken to Bangabandhu Sheikh Mujib Medical University Hospital from Dhaka Central Jail Sunday night after he complained of chest pains. The Chief Metropolitan Magistrate's Court for Dhaka sent Jalil to jail Sunday after his four-day remand ended. Joint forces arrested Jalil at his Mercantile Bank office in Dilkhusha on May 28 with suspected links to corruption and sabotage. He was taken on a four-day remand on May 29. bdnews24.
